# BaliBuddy PWA - Project Rules & Standards

## 🎯 Project Identity
**App Name:** BaliBuddy
**Type:** Progressive Web App (PWA) - Offline-First Travel Companion for Backpackers in Bali
**Primary Language:** German (de) - All UI text must be in German by default

## 🚫 STRICTLY FORBIDDEN - Web-Only Stack
These native modules are BANNED and will break the web build:
- ❌ @rnmapbox/maps (use maplibre-gl or react-map-gl instead)
- ❌ react-native-vision-camera (use react-webcam + tesseract.js for OCR)
- ❌ expo-notifications (use standard Web Push API with Service Workers)
- ❌ Any other native module without web support

## ✅ REQUIRED Tech Stack
- **Framework:** Expo SDK 55 with react-native-web
- **Routing:** Expo Router (src/app directory)
- **Styling:** NativeWind v5 (Tailwind CSS)
- **Database:** WatermelonDB with LokiJS (IndexedDB) adapter
- **Maps:** maplibre-gl or react-map-gl (Web compatible)
- **OCR:** react-webcam + tesseract.js
- **Localization:** i18next-react (German primary, infinitely scalable)
- **Icons:** lucide-react-native
- **Offline:** Service Workers with aggressive caching

## 🎨 UI/UX Philosophy: "Bright, Airy & Bento-Grid"
**Visual Identity:**
- Light Mode ONLY (no dark mode in MVP)
- Tropical teal (#00B4D8) - primary accent
- Rice-paddy green (#90BE6D) - success/nature
- Coral sunset (#FF6B6B) - alerts/warnings
- Clean white backgrounds with subtle shadows
- Rounded corners (16px-24px border radius)

**Layout System:**
- Bento-Grid card-based design
- 4-column grid on desktop, 2-column on mobile
- Consistent 16px spacing between cards
- Cards: white background, subtle shadow, hover effects
- Never clutter screens - maximum 6-8 cards visible

**Typography:**
- System font stack (SF Pro, Inter, sans-serif)
- Headlines: Bold, 24-32px
- Body: Regular, 16px
- Captions: 14px, muted color

## 🌍 Internationalization (CRITICAL)
- Default UI: German (de)
- Toggle to English (en) as proof of concept
- JSON structure must be infinitely scalable for: es, fr, ja, etc.
- All text, menus, placeholders in German by default
- Translation keys: nested objects by feature

## 📱 PWA Requirements
- public/manifest.json with "display": "standalone"
- Service Worker for offline caching
- "Add to Home Screen" (A2HS) prompt for iOS Safari
- Works fully offline in "dense jungle" scenarios
- IndexedDB for all persistent data

## 🔧 Development Standards
- TypeScript strict mode
- Functional components only
- Hooks over HOCs
- Async/await for all API calls
- Error boundaries on all screens
- Loading states for all async operations
- Offline indicators when data is stale

## 📊 Database Schema Guidelines
- All models must have: id, created_at, updated_at
- Soft deletes (isDeleted flag) over hard deletes
- Indexed fields for queries used in UI
- Pre-seed static data (phrases, prices, etc.)

## 🎯 Feature Implementation Priority
1. Offline-first (all features work without internet)
2. German language support
3. Bento-Grid UI consistency
4. PWA capabilities (installable, cached)
5. Live data when available (currency, weather)

## 🧪 Testing Requirements
- Web builds must pass: `npm run web`
- No console errors in production build
- Offline functionality verified
- German text displaying correctly
- Responsive on 320px to 1920px screens

## 📁 File Structure
```
src/
├── app/                 # Expo Router pages
├── components/          # Reusable UI components
├── constants/           # Colors, sizes, strings
├── db/                  # WatermelonDB models & schema
├── hooks/               # Custom React hooks
├── i18n/                # Translation files (de.json, en.json)
├── services/            # API clients, external services
├── types/               # TypeScript type definitions
└── utils/               # Helper functions
public/
├── manifest.json        # PWA manifest
├── sw.js               # Service Worker
└── icons/              # App icons for PWA
```

## 🚀 Build Commands
- `npm install` - Install dependencies
- `npm run web` - Start web development server
- `npm run build:web` - Production build

## ⚠️ Common Pitfalls to Avoid
- Adding native modules without web support
- Hardcoding text instead of using i18n keys
- Forgetting offline states in UI
- Cluttering the Bento-Grid layout
- Using dark colors on main screens
- Skipping loading/error states

